data.enText: always behaving in the same way, or having the same opinions, standards, etc.
She's not very consistent in the way she treats her children.

data.chText: 他是米兰队这个赛季状态最稳定的队员。
data.enText: He has been Milan's most consistent player this season.

data.chText: 我们在实施这些规则时必须保持一致。
data.enText: We must be consistent in applying the rules.
a consistent approach to the problem
happening in the same way and continuing for a period of time

data.chText: 这个政党长时期的提不出任何新政策
data.enText: the party's consistent failure to come up with any new policies
a pattern of consistent growth in the economy

data.chText: 与…一致的；相符的；符合的；不矛盾的
data.enText: in agreement with sth; not contradicting sth

data.chText: 这些结果与我们早些时候的研究完全吻合。
data.enText: The results are entirely consistent with our earlier research.

data.chText: 和从楼上摔下来的情形相符合的伤处
data.enText: injuries consistent with a fall from an upper storey (= similar to those such a fall would have caused)

before.enText: of an argument or a set of ideas

data.enText: having different parts that all agree with each other

data.chText: 经过深思熟虑的、相互连贯的论点
她的工作一直是高水准的。
data.enText: Her work has been of a consistently high standard.

data.chText: 我们一直坚持不懈地鼓吹要更改法律。
data.enText: We have argued consistently for a change in the law.

tr: marked by an orderly, logical, and aesthetically consistent relation of parts
(sometimes followed by `with') in agreement or consistent or reliable
example: testimony consistent with the known facts
I have decided that the course of conduct which I am following is consistent with my sense of responsibility as president in time of war"- FD

tr: the same throughout in structure or composition
example: bituminous coal is often treated as a consistent and homogeneous product
astonishingly reproducible results can be obtained

value.def: Someone who is consistent always behaves in the same way, has the same attitudes towards people or things, or achieves the same level of success in something.

example.ex: Becker has never been the most consistent of players anyway.
example.tran: 不管怎么说，贝克尔从来就不是表现最为稳定的球员。
他对自由贸易始终如一的支持

value.tran: (行为、态度等)一贯的，一致的，始终如一的

example.ex: It's something I have consistently denied...
example.tran: 那是我自始至终否认的事。

example.ex: Jones and Armstrong maintain a consistently high standard.
example.tran: 琼斯和阿姆斯特朗始终保持着高水准。

value.def: If one fact or idea is consistent with another, they do not contradict each other.

example.ex: This result is consistent with the findings of Garnett & Tobin...
example.tran: 这个结果与加尼特托宾公司的调查结果一致。

example.ex: New goals are not always consistent with the existing policies.
example.tran: 新目标并不总是与现行政策一致。

value.tran: （观点等）一致的，吻合的，不矛盾的

value.def: An argument or set of ideas that is consistent is one in which no part contradicts or conflicts with any other part.

example.ex: These are clear consistent policies which we are putting into place.
example.tran: 这些就是我们正在付诸实施的政策，不但清楚而且前后一致。

value.tran: (观点或看法)前后一致的，连贯的
